OL,3,CKnife crime campaigner Pooja Kanda
OL,4,Cgiven OBE in King's Birthday honours
OL,6,F"I know that the OBE is in my name,
OL,7,Fbut this is for my son.
OL,9,F"I'm only here because of who he was.
OL,10,FHe was such a kind, loving, caring,
OL,11,Fnot a son, not a brother, a human
OL,12,Fbeing, a person who everyone loved."
OL,14,FMs Kanda said she was driven to
OL,15,Fcampaign after witnessing the trial of
OL,16,Fher son's killers, who attacked the 16-
OL,17,Fyear-old in a case of mistaken
OL,18,Fidentity.
OL,20,FThey had been able to buy knives
OL,21,Fwithout identity checks.
